KATHMANDU, MARCH 25

Pratima Rana Pande, Honorary Consul General of Italy to Nepal, recently met Pope Leo XIV at the Vatican, marking a notable engagement in diplomatic and cultural relations.

googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1687249846701-0'); });

Related Articles In Pictures: 'Squid Game' meets election campaign in Kathmandu England survives Italy scare to reach Super Eights at T20 World Cup, Afghanistan registers first win

googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1687249883356-0'); });

Pande, who has contributed to strengthening Nepal-Italy ties, was earlier honoured with the Order of the Star of Italy, one of Italy's highest civilian distinctions. The award was conferred by Italian Ambassador Vincenzo de Luca at an event in Kathmandu on October 22, 2021.

The Order of the Star of Italy is one of the Italian state's highest civilian honours, awarded to individuals-both Italians abroad and foreign nationals-who have made significant contributions to promoting friendly relations, cooperation, and cultural ties with Italy.

